        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 10:52PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1050 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated strong to severe
thunderstorms along a line extending from 7 miles east of Luther to
near Stanton to near Middleville. Movement was east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph with higher gusts possible.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and damage
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Pleasant Valley around 1120 PM EDT.
Oil City around 1125 PM EDT.
Coleman around 1130 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Carrollton,
Garfield, Arthur, Fenmore, Crump, Buena Vista Township, Gera,
Indiantown, Bombay, and Hemlock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
